# GitLab MCP Server Settings
# Use this file to configure the GitLab MCP server for Claude Desktop
#
# Format:
# SETTING_NAME=value
#
# Required Settings:
# -----------------
# GITLAB_TOKEN - Your GitLab Personal Access Token
#   Generate a token at: https://gitlab.com/-/profile/personal_access_tokens
#   Required scopes: api, read_api, read_repository, write_repository
#   This token is required for the GitLab MCP server to function
#
# Optional Settings:
# -----------------
# GITLAB_URL - GitLab instance URL (default: https://gitlab.com)
#   For self-hosted GitLab, set this to your instance URL
# DOCKER_IMAGE - Docker image name and tag (default: mcp/gitlab:latest)
# RESTART_CLAUDE - Whether to restart Claude Desktop if it's running (true/false, default: true)
#
# Examples:
# GITLAB_TOKEN=glpat-xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
# GITLAB_URL=https://gitlab.example.com
# DOCKER_IMAGE=mcp/gitlab:custom
# RESTART_CLAUDE=false
#
# Default settings (uncomment and modify as needed):
GITLAB_TOKEN=
# GITLAB_URL=https://gitlab.com
# DOCKER_IMAGE=mcp/gitlab:latest
# RESTART_CLAUDE=true
